The scientific and commercial use of the World Wide Web has caused far-reaching changes in information technology and has had a great influence on medical computing. Web browsers are becoming a universal starting point for all kinds of client-server applications. Many commercial and medical systems - such as information or reservation systems are being shifted towards web-based systems. This paper describes new techniques for implementing medical web-based applications and provides a classification of these techniques. Securtity problems are the main topics for further developments in medical computing.  
